-- Kristin Armstrong of U.S. Wins Olympic Cycling Time-Trial Gold
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-08-01T13:02:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/kristin-armstrong-of-u-s-wins-olympic-cycling-time-trial-gold.html
Kristin Armstrong of the U.S. won her
second consecutive gold medal in the women’s Olympic cycling
time trial.  World champion Judith Arndt of  Germany  was second, and
Russia’s Olga Zabelinskaya came third.  Armstrong completed the 18-mile course in 37 minutes 35
seconds, winning by about 15 seconds at Hampton Court, south of
London.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  